**** INSTALLATION *****
-----------------------------------
Downloading and Installing ProofPower
-----------------------------------

Go to 

 http://www.lemma-one.com/ProofPower/getting/versions/

and install ProofPower

------------------------------------
Downloading and Installing required Libraries 
-----------------------------------
Go to the parent directory of psgraph, 
  cd ..

Get the isaplib library (requires git)

  git clone git://github.com/Quantomatic/isaplib.git

Next, get the quantomatic library (requires git)

  git clone git://github.com/Quantomatic/quantomatic.git
  cd quantomatic
  git checkout scala-frontend
  git pull
  

------------------------------------
Building isaplib + quanto + psgraph on the top of pp
-----------------------------------  

Create a pp db/heap based on zed theory
  pp_make_database -p zed $PPHOME/db/zed_psgraph

clean up previous bulid
  find . -type d -name .polysave | xargs rm -rf
  find . -type f -name *.heap | xargs rm -rf
  
go to the build direcory:
  cd PSGRAPHDIR/src/provers/proofpower/build

start pp with the fresh empty db
  pp -d zed_psgraph

in the poly ml interface: 
build isap + quanto + psgraph
  use "PRELOAD.ml";
load the built heap
  PolyML.SaveState.loadState "supertac_psgraph.heap";
run testing, should be no exceptions or any error messages:
  use "test.ml"
save and exit pp;
  save_and_exit 0;





